      "content": "fair enough, but aren't you just looking at it through a lens of \"avoiding mistakes\" rather than \"achieving objectives\"? if the objective was regime change and the dictator is gone, isn't that an objective success, even if the aftermath is messy? it feels like you're dismissing the actual strategic aim achieved by the coalition.",
